{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, high dimensional homological features are unattainable due to computational cost, and in any case, the sensitivity of PDs to sampling or noise is not well understood in high dimensions.",
    "This makes learning the underlying topology of the data for use in deep neural networks challenging.",
    "The need for a good backpropagation strategy The differentiability of PDs or other homological quantities is not guaranteed or necessarily well understood.",
    "This makes backpropagation in deep neural networks that incorporate topological signatures extremely challenging or only feasible under special conditions (Moor et al. 2020).",
    "Capturing multi-variate persistence In some cases, multiple concurrent filtrations are needed to fully capture the topology of the data manifold, especially for data in higher dimensions."
  ]
}